@prat0318 See if this satisfies the zipkin decorator use case. I'll add unit tests and docs once the interface looks good.  It is unfortunate that we can't use the same decorator pattern we've been using for wrapping ``Client``, ``Resource`` and ``Operation`` since the point of instrumentation is internal to the ``HttpFuture``.

Reponse callbacks
```python
def foo(incoming_response, operation):
    print 'foo'

request_options = {
    'response_callbacks': [foo]    
}

client = Swagger.from_url(...)
pet = client.pet.getPet(petId=1234, _request_options=request_options).result()
```

**Edit**: Removed client-wide response callbacks since client decorators can insert additional callbacks in their respective operation decorator.

